The paper discusses techniques for extracting data from the Web, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research. The use of logic-based techniques suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the focus on robustness and reliability suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
